T1  - Estimation of a fixed-effect Cobb–Douglas system using panel data
AU  - Schmidt, Peter
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 37
IS  - 3
SP  - 361
EP  - 380
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/03/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(88)90011-5
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407688900115
AB  - This paper considers the estimation of a model consisting of a Cobb–Douglas production function and the associated first-order conditions for cost minimization. There is a fixed individual (firm) effect in each equation, and the availability of panel data is assumed. The conditional MLE is derived and shown to be MLE after a within transformation. It can be written explicitly as a corrected OLS estimator or as an IV estimator. In the special case in which the errors in the production function are independent of the errors in the first-order conditions, the conditional MLE does not require input price data.
