AB  - For a first-order autoregressive model with unknown intercept and normal errors the mean and variance of the finite-sample distribution of the least-squares estimator of the autoregressive parameter are numerically computed using formulae for evaluating the first and second moments of a ratio of two quadratic forms in normally distributed variables. Previous results in the literature are corrected and results for the case where the value of the autoregressive parameter is near unity in absolute value are presented.
